  "text": "The detectability of markers sets a limit to the type of products that are suitable. RFID transponders are manufactured as small as 50 Â 50 lm, so-called RFID dust, and transponders could thus be added to mineral powders, given that the transponders themselves are not a problem for the customers. However, since small transponders usually have lower read rates [CITATION_1] and have shorter read ranges, small transponders may be hard to detect and the reader environment must be adapted accordingly.",
